p: Another possible explanation for the lack of dengue in Kisumu and Nairobi could be the density of Ae. aegypti populations. Although the Ae. aegypti density in Nairobi, was about half of that observed in Kisumu and Mombasa, and might also be one of the reasons for the lack of dengue in Nairobi, the density of Ae. aegypti was similar in Mombasa and Kisumu, so Ae. aegypti density would not explain the lack of outbreaks in Kisumu.
